1 Pour a little oil into a non-stick frying pan
2 Heat the oil over medium heat on the stove
3 Put a beef patty into the skillet and cook until done
4 Move and flip the patty every couple of minutes using spatula
5 When cooked throughout place a slice of cheese on the patty and let it melt
6 Turn off the stove
7 Remove the patty from the pan using a spatula 
8 Place the burger onto the bottom half of a bun
9 Slice a tomato into fairly thin slices 
10 Separate a few pieces of lettuce and cut them in half
11 Put the tomato slices and lettuce slices on top of the burger
12 Garnish with condiments, ketchup, mayo, ranch and mustard
13 Top with the remaining bun half
-1 Unknown
